Definition: ready and able to resort to force or violence
Example: pugnacious spirits...lamented that there was so little prospect of an exhilarating disturbance- Herman Melville; they were rough and determined fighting men
Synonyms: noun, attribute, pugnacity, rough, state, roughness, ready, and, able, to, resort, force, or, violence, spirits, lamented, that, there, was, so, little, prospect, of, an, exhilarating, disturbance, -, Herman, Melville, they, were, determined, fighting, men
Category: adj.all
